  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dad\u0db4\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca 390\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d88\u0dad \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd6 55 \u0db6\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "55 are rescued in a storm 390 nautical miles away",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Navy says that 55 people who were on a multi-day fishing vessel that got caught in a typhoon in the deep sea about 390 nautical miles south-east of Sri Lanka while they were illegally migrating from Sri Lanka to a foreign country were rescued.",
        "The group was brought to Hambantota port today (12) and the operation was carried out according to a notification given by the Department of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources to the Colombo Maritime Search and Rescue Coordination Center that a multi-day fishing vessel was floating in the deep sea south-east of Sri Lanka. The army says.",
        "The navy ship Parakramabahu, which immediately responded to the notification, was dispatched to the sea area where the distressed fishing vessel was located for a search and rescue operation and 46 men along with 05 smugglers were aboard the multi-day fishing vessel which was floating very dangerously due to the extreme roughness of the deep sea area. , 55 people, including 3 women and 6 children, were rescued safely, the Navy said.",
        "The Navy said that the fishing vessel used for this illegal migration was in danger of sinking due to the damage to the hull caused by a storm in the deep sea, and the sea water seeped into the vessel and the vessel was in a critical condition after being stranded in the deep sea for several days due to lack of food and water. mentions",
        "The Navy said that the persons taken into custody by the Navy were given first aid and other facilities in the ship Parakramabahu and brought to the Hambantota port. The navy also mentioned that due to excessive seawater seeping into the distressed fishing vessel, it was abandoned without being able to bring them to the land.",
        "The Navy said that these people, aged between 3 and 54, were identified as residents of Trincomalee, Mannar, Vavuniya, Kilinochichiya, Mullaitivu, Jaffna and Kalpitiya and that the group will be handed over to the Hambantota Port Police for further legal proceedings. said more."
      ],
